Key Aspects of LLMsDefinition: A type of Generative AI designed to recognize and predict text sequences.Underlying Technology: Built on "transformer models" which analyze relationships between words in large datasets.Capabilities: Capable of writing, summarizing, translating, and answering complex questions.Examples: Popular models include ChatGPT (OpenAI), Gemini (Google), Claude (Anthropic), and Meta AI.Specialized Models: Examples include Pathumma LLM, designed for Thai language and context.Risks: LLMs can produce "hallucinations" (false information) and require verification of output.Key ApplicationsContent Generation: Creating articles, reports, and creative writing.Coding Assistance: Helping developers write and debug code.Customer Support: Powering chatbots for instant replies.Data Analysis: Summarizing documents and analyzing text-based data.This video shows a deep dive into how LLMs are trained on powerful GPUs:


LimitationsHallucination: LLMs may confidently generate false information.Bias: They can reflect biases present in their training data.Context Understanding: While advanced, they do not possess human-like reasoning or true understanding.